Libre graph-oriented photo editor

About
-----
Mikado is a graph-oriented photo editor based on GEGL.
Mikado is a generic library for creating patching environments.
(such as flowcanvas)
It is not yet in a working state for now.

License
-------
Mikado is free software; you can redistribute it and/or modify it under the terms of the GNU Lesser General Public License and GNU General Public License as published by the Free Software Foundation; either version 3 of the Licenses, or (at your option) any later version. The library itself is licensed under LGPL while the commandline application is licensed under GPL.

Future directions
-----------------
The Mikado library could allow us to create patching environments for different backends that can be used in graph-oriented way:

 * GEGL (image effects)
 * GLSL shaders
 * SpatOsc
 * libpd
 * libmapper
 * Pyo

